'''91.1 ABC Central Victoria''' (call sign: '''3ABCRR''') is an [[ABC Local Radio]] station based in [[Bendigo, Victoria]].<ref name="aboutus">{{cite web |title=About ABC Central Victoria |url=http://www.abc.net.au/centralvic/about.htm |date=2007-03-05 |accessdate=2007-12-04 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20071012173212/http://abc.net.au/centralvic/about.htm <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-10-12}}</ref> The station opened in January 1993 and covers Bendigo, [[Echuca, Victoria|Echuca]], [[St Arnaud, Victoria|St Arnaud]] and [[Kyneton, Victoria|Kyneton]].<ref name="aboutus" />

The station's local programming includes a breakfast show presented by Jonathan Ridnell on weekdays and Simon Rogers on Saturdays, and a weekday morning program hosted by Fiona Parker (also heard on [[ABC Western Victoria]]).<ref name="aboutus" />

